data.title: Summitville Depot 1972.
data.meta_description: Taken by me with a Kodak 128 Instamatic. This was the New York Ontario and Western depot in Summitville, NY. It was a Borscht Belt stop. At this time someone was attempting to start a tourist railroad here. It did not come to fruition. They had brought in a boxcar shown here and some other equipment. They also built a corregated metal shed and laid sonme track. All this is now gone.
